The paper discusses the current state-of-the-art of massive antenna array architectures, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the physical size and cost of the hardware, which is related to augmented reality (cs.AR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the merging of two cellular concepts, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
